This project is a monorepo of multiple NextJS apps. It uses Vercel's TurboRepo to build, test, and deploy.

### Apps and utilities:

Before running any terminal command including pnpm, make sure to be in the correct folder.

- ./apps/log - logging and observability app
- ./apps/trade - day trading and investment positions management
- ./apps/data - common files imported by other apps, mostly helping with user and database management, but also containing useful utilities, functions, components, and server actions to accomplish various tasks and integrate with 3rd party services

- ./apps/data/sql - functions, types, and interfaces for interacting with databases
- ./apps/data/twillio - integration with Twillio to send logs and alerts via SMS message
- ./apps/data/src - client-side React components, hooks, and utility functions
- ./apps/data/cc - saves console logs to the cloud after printing them in the terminal

### PNPM instead of NPM:

If you need to run `npm i` or `npm install`, run `pnpm install` instead.

### Import paths:

./apps/log and ./apps/trade use project-relative import paths to reference their own root project directory, like `@/src/path/to/file`

./apps/data is used as common library of utilities, so it must always use relative import paths like `../../`, because this will work when imported by any other app
